claim.claim-text:
1. A method of generating a stereo signal, the method comprising:
receiving a down-mixed mono signal;
decoding the down-mixed mono signal;
decoding a parameter that represents an energy difference between channels of the stereo signal;
decoding a parameter that represents a phase difference between channels of the stereo signal; and
up-mixing the decoded down-mixed mono signal by using the decoded parameters, to generate the stereo signal.

3. A method of generating a stereo signal, the method comprising:
receiving a down-mixed mono signal;
decoding the down-mixed mono signal;
decoding a parameter that represents an energy difference between channels of the stereo signal;
decoding a parameter that represents a phase difference between channels of the stereo signal;
generating a parameter representing a phase difference between one of the stereo signal and the down-mixed mono signal; and
up-mixing the decoded down-mixed mono signal by using the decoded parameters and the generated parameter, to generate the stereo signal.
